org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.staging

Class PartitionedStagingCommitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.OutputCommitter
      • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.lib.output.PathOutputCommitter
        • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.AbstractS3ACommitter
          • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.staging.StagingCommitter
            • org.apache.hadoop.fs.s3a.commit.staging.PartitionedStagingCommitter

  • public class PartitionedStagingCommitter
extends StagingCommitter
    Partitioned committer. This writes data to specific "partition" subdirectories, applying conflict resolution on a partition-by-partition basis. The existence and state of any parallel partitions for which there is no are output files are not considered in the conflict resolution. The conflict policy is
    • FAIL: fail the commit if any of the partitions have data.
    • APPEND: add extra data to the destination partitions.
    • REPLACE: delete the destination partition in the job commit (i.e. after and only if all tasks have succeeded.

        Job-side conflict resolution. The partition path conflict resolution actions are:
        1. FAIL: assume checking has taken place earlier; no more checks.
        2. APPEND: allowed.; no need to check.
        3. REPLACE deletes all existing partitions.
